  <div class="flex justify-center pt-12 pb-4 ">
    <h1 class="text-center text-8xl lg:text-4xl font-display text-white-light font-bold lg:tracking-wider">Wheat</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="px-20 xl:mx-24 2xl:mx-72 flex-1 overflow-y-auto text-justify">
    <!-- How good is it ? -->
    <div class="xl:px-20 flex flex-col lg:items-center justify-center text-justify text-2xl lg:text-base tracking-wider text-white-light">
      <div class="pb-8 lg:pt-4">
        <h3 class="text-4xl lg:text-lg font-display text-white-light text-center">How good is it ?</h3>
        <p class="pt-4">Some of the most nutritious parts of the grain — <span class="text-white-darker font-bold tracking-wider">the bran and germ</span> - are absent from white wheat because they’re removed during the milling & refining process. <br>Therefore, white wheat is <span class="italic">relatively poor</span> in many vitamins and minerals (very small amounts of <span class="text-white-darker font-bold tracking-wider">vitamins and minerals</span>, <span class="text-white-darker font-bold tracking-wider">iron, potassium</span> and <span class="text-white-darker font-bold tracking-wider">B vitamins</span>)<span class="text-white-darker font-bold tracking-wider">compared to whole-grain wheat</span>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mx-40 lg:mx-12 mt-12 lg:mt-0 text-center lg:w-2/5">
        <p class="italic text-lg lg:text-sm">For 100g of wheat</p>
        <ul class="mx-10 flex flex-col items-center">
          <li>Water : <span class="font-bold">11%</span></li>
          <li>Protein : <span class="font-bold">13.2g</span></li>
          <li>Carbs : <span class="font-bold">72g</span></li>
          <li>Sugar : <span class="font-bold">0.4g</span></li>
          <li>Fiber : <span class="font-bold">10.7g</span></li>
          <li>Fat : <span class="font-bold">2.5g</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lg:flex lg:justify-center lg:items-start lg:px-20">
    <!-- A bit of history -->
      <div data-controller="dropdown" class="pt-20 lg:pt-10 lg:mr-16 lg:w-1/2 flex flex-col justify-center">
        <a data-action="click->dropdown#toggle" class="flex justify-around items-center w-full border-4 lg:border-2 lg:border-white-light shadow-md rounded-md" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="pl-8 py-4 lg:py-0 text-4xl lg:text-xl font-display text-white-light text-center">A bit of history...</span>
          <div data-dropdown-target="arrow_closed" class="py-8 lg:py-2 w-12 lg:w-8">
            <svg fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 134 153"><path d="M61.924 113.996L3.794 55.92a7.167 7.167 0 010-10.142l6.78-6.774a7.183 7.183 0 0110.14-.012L67 85.018l46.285-46.026a7.183 7.183 0 0110.14.012l6.78 6.774a7.166 7.166 0 010 10.142l-58.129 58.076a7.185 7.185 0 01-10.152 0z" fill="#fff"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div data-dropdown-target="arrow_opened" class="py-8 lg:py-2 w-12 lg:w-8 hidden">
            <svg fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 448 512"><path d="M240.971 130.524l194.343 194.343c9.373 9.373 9.373 24.569 0 33.941l-22.667 22.667c-9.357 9.357-24.522 9.375-33.901.04L224 227.495 69.255 381.516c-9.379 9.335-24.544 9.317-33.901-.04l-22.667-22.667c-9.373-9.373-9.373-24.569 0-33.941L207.03 130.525c9.372-9.373 24.568-9.373 33.941-.001z" fill="#fff"/></svg>
          </div>
        </a>

        <div data-dropdown-target="dropdown" class="pt-12 lg:pt-4 flex justify-center text-justify text-2xl lg:text-base tracking-wider text-white-light hidden">
         <p>The cultivation of wheat was traced back to south east <b>Turkey</b> some 10,000 years ago. Cultivated wheat came to southern <b>Europe, Egypt</b> and <b>India</b> by 6000 BCE, <b>Germany</b> and <b>Spain</b> by 5000 BCE and by 3000 BCE, it had reached <b>England</b> and <b>Scandinavia</b>.
          <br><br>Modern wheat was cultivated from ancient wheat species such as <span class="text-white-darker font-bold tracking-wider">einkorn</span>, <span class="text-white-darker font-bold tracking-wider">emmer</span> and <span class="text-white-darker font-bold tracking-wider">spelt wheat</span>.
          <br><br>Wheat is <span class="italic">able to be grown</span> in almost <span class="italic">every climate and elevation</span>, which is why wheat is grown on more land area worldwide than any other food crop.
          <br><br>Due to its versatility, high in carbohydrates, and with <span class="italic">more protein than in corn and rice</span>, wheat is a relatively cheap and easily attainable source of energy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

